<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Steering - Steering Column - Removal and Installation</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="9">
        <title>Removal and Installation</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Steering Wheel</title>
            <table id="t1104002">
                <title>Special Tool</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.16*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.84*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <graphic filename="../figST2/ST2729A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="152px"
                                         scalefitheight="112px"/>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remover, Steering Wheel</para>
                                <para>ZTSE4229 or equivalent</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the wheels are in the straight-ahead position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery ground cable. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S08/S08307.htm" bookname="S08307">Battery, Mounting and Cables in
                        S08307</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel horn pad from the steering wheel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the horn ground wire and remove the 4 screws, then remove the horn switch
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1104005" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025279.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel retaining nut.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 45 Nm (33 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Index-mark the steering wheel to the steering shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1104006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025280.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using the special tool, remove the steering wheel.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1104007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025282.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Lubricate the steering wheel hub and the multifunction switch bushing with multi-purpose
                    grease.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Steering Column Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel. For additional information, refer to Steering Wheel in this
                    section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the cab forward.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Index-mark the steering shaft to the steering gear, then remove the steering shaft pinch
                    nut and bolt.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; Disconnect the steering shaft from the steering gear.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1104008" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025283.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the cab.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 3 steering column cover screws, then remove the 2 steering column covers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1104009" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025284.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 6 steering shaft cover screws, then remove the steering shaft cover rear
                    half.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1104010" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025285.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the following 4 electrical connectors:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Ignition switch</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Key-in-ignition switch</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Turn signal/head lamp switch</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Windshield wiper switch</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 2 steering column bracket lower bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 2 steering column bracket upper nuts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering column.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Steering Column Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the steering shaft sliding joint with multi-purpose grease.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1104011" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025286.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the steering column, connecting the steering shaft to the steering gear.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the 2 bracket bolts and the 2 bracket nuts.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Do not tighten the fasteners at this time.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the 2 bolts and the 2 nuts to 16 Nm (12 lb-ft) in the sequence shown.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1104012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025160.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the cab forward and install the steering shaft pinch bolt and nut.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Tighten to 16 Nm (12 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the cab and connect the 4 electrical connectors.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the steering shaft cover rear half and install the 6 screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the 2 steering column covers and install the 3 screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the steering wheel. For additional information, refer to Steering Wheel in this
                    section.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
